WEBVTT

00:07.920 --> 00:09.879
- I don't want pity votes.
- Why not?

00:09.922 --> 00:11.837
They count just as much
as regular votes.

00:11.881 --> 00:13.274
- The election
is in three days!

00:13.317 --> 00:15.015
What are we gonna do?

00:15.058 --> 00:16.799
[xylophone chimes]

00:16.842 --> 00:19.541
- We will be instituting
a dress code.

00:19.584 --> 00:22.239
No jackets!

00:22.283 --> 00:24.285
- Let's cut class.

00:24.328 --> 00:26.461
- Can I help you,
Ms. Valdovinos?

00:26.504 --> 00:28.419
- What did happen
between you two?

00:28.463 --> 00:30.160
- We were in love.

00:30.204 --> 00:31.770
- I will play Juliet,

00:31.814 --> 00:34.208
and the rest will be peasants.

00:34.251 --> 00:35.209
[indistinct chatter]

00:35.252 --> 00:36.601
- Juliet?

00:36.645 --> 00:39.169
- A tomboy Juliet!

00:39.213 --> 00:40.910
A maimed Romeo!

00:40.953 --> 00:44.174
We are really going
to shake things up around here.

00:44.218 --> 00:45.480
- We'll just have
to find another way

00:45.523 --> 00:48.091
to get people's attention.

00:48.135 --> 00:49.527
They want to pit us
against each other

00:49.571 --> 00:50.876
so they can control us!

00:50.920 --> 00:52.748
- Sorry, Teach!
- Ah! Hey, no!

00:52.791 --> 00:55.359
- See what we can do
when we work together?

00:55.403 --> 00:56.447
- You know something?

00:56.491 --> 00:58.188
I'm starting like school.

00:58.232 --> 00:59.929
[classic rock music]

01:03.411 --> 01:05.282
- First, you'll have to know
what happens

01:05.325 --> 01:07.545
when an atomic bomb explodes.

01:07.589 --> 01:09.156
You'll know when it comes.

01:09.199 --> 01:12.115
We hope it never comes,
but you must get ready.

01:12.159 --> 01:14.770
Be like Burt.
When there is a flash,

01:14.813 --> 01:17.120
duck, and cover,
and do it fast.

01:17.164 --> 01:20.254
If you are not ready
and do not know what to do,

01:20.297 --> 01:22.256
it could hurt you
in different ways.

01:22.299 --> 01:24.997
It could knock you down hard
or throw you against...

01:25.041 --> 01:26.564
- If the bomb does drop,
you're all welcome

01:26.608 --> 01:28.000
to stay
in my bomb shelter.

01:28.044 --> 01:30.090
It seats 35, but there's
only enough food for six,

01:30.133 --> 01:32.570
so BYOF.

01:32.614 --> 01:33.876
- Jane's got momentum.

01:33.919 --> 01:35.399
People's minds are made up.

01:35.443 --> 01:38.402
- So we'll change them.

01:38.446 --> 01:41.797
We have to.

01:41.840 --> 01:43.233
- Hey, you know,
maybe the U.S.

01:43.277 --> 01:45.017
could have handed out
turtle shells in Hiroshima.

01:45.061 --> 01:47.063
I would've done it,
but my family and I

01:47.107 --> 01:49.718
were busy being imprisoned
by our own government.

01:51.198 --> 01:52.590
- Forget the bomb!

01:52.634 --> 01:56.027
Wait till we light up the sky
tonight with these!

01:56.072 --> 01:59.509
- We are going to pull
so many pranks.

01:59.554 --> 02:00.859
- No pranks
at the drive-in tonight.

02:00.903 --> 02:02.470
I want to watch the movie.

02:02.513 --> 02:04.733
- You want to watch it
next to me, sweetheart?

02:04.776 --> 02:06.865
- [sighs] Fine.

02:06.909 --> 02:08.824
Hey, Nancy,
Gil's gonna give us a ride.

02:08.866 --> 02:11.218
- Oh.
- Me three! Me three!

02:13.437 --> 02:15.483
- They never saw it coming.

02:15.526 --> 02:17.353
- What's hitting you, Facciano?

02:17.398 --> 02:18.486
- I just have this feeling

02:18.529 --> 02:19.791
something bad
is gonna happen tonight.

02:19.835 --> 02:21.706
- Not on my watch.

02:21.750 --> 02:23.055
Halloween is my Christmas.

02:23.099 --> 02:24.883
- Yeah, relax,
the election's in the bag

02:24.927 --> 02:26.798
after we got
everyone's jackets back.

02:26.841 --> 02:28.235
- Buddy would need
a miracle to win.

02:28.278 --> 02:30.150
- I know.
I know.

02:30.193 --> 02:31.629
Everything's good.

02:31.673 --> 02:34.937
The election, Richie.

02:34.980 --> 02:39.246
But it's always calmest
right before the storm.

02:39.289 --> 02:41.161
[pensive music]

02:41.204 --> 02:44.251
- So let's be ready every day,
all the time,

02:44.293 --> 02:48.385
to do the right thing
if the atomic bomb explodes.

02:48.429 --> 02:50.257
Duck and cover.

02:50.300 --> 02:53.173
- ♪ Oh, the bomb
is gonna drop ♪

02:53.216 --> 02:56.045
♪ Don't know when,
I don't know why ♪

02:56.088 --> 02:58.829
♪ It's the calm before chaos

02:58.874 --> 03:01.790
♪ Fire in the sky

03:01.833 --> 03:04.619
♪ If the bomb
comes choosing you ♪

03:04.662 --> 03:07.448
♪ It will light up
all your life ♪

03:07.491 --> 03:10.233
♪ One eye open for the boom

03:10.277 --> 03:12.975
♪ Fire in the sky

03:13.018 --> 03:14.716
♪ Oh, since the dawn of time

03:14.759 --> 03:16.239
♪ The element of surprise

03:16.283 --> 03:18.981
♪ Had landed on the guys
who just ignored the signs ♪

03:19.024 --> 03:21.853
♪ So I won't close my eyes
to titanic ice ♪

03:21.897 --> 03:24.378
♪ When disaster strikes

03:24.421 --> 03:27.032
- ♪ Don't lose your cool,
fighter jets ain't coming ♪

03:27.076 --> 03:29.513
both: ♪ Oh, but if they do,
there's no use in running ♪

03:29.557 --> 03:32.473
♪ So get in the mood,
live until we're done in ♪

03:32.516 --> 03:36.216
♪ And give in to the boom

03:36.259 --> 03:43.179
♪

03:44.006 --> 03:47.488
♪ Give in to the boom

03:47.531 --> 03:54.668
♪

03:55.496 --> 03:58.281
♪ Give in to the boom

03:58.325 --> 04:00.936
- ♪ If the bomb is gonna drop

04:00.979 --> 04:03.808
♪ Pour a drink
and toast to life ♪

04:03.852 --> 04:06.724
- ♪ Don't say that,
it's surely not ♪

04:06.768 --> 04:09.727
♪ All I see is blue sky

04:09.771 --> 04:11.207
- ♪ I know
you're probably right ♪

04:11.251 --> 04:13.905
♪ I probably need a night
with just a little fun ♪

04:13.949 --> 04:15.298
♪ And maybe with the one

04:15.342 --> 04:18.345
♪ So let me close my eyes
to titanic ice,

04:18.387 --> 04:20.521
♪ Baby, roll that dice

04:20.564 --> 04:23.306
all: ♪ Don't lose your cool,
fighter jets ain't coming ♪

04:23.350 --> 04:26.091
♪ Oh, but if they do,
there's no use in running ♪

04:26.135 --> 04:28.964
♪ So get in the mood,
live until we're done in ♪

04:29.007 --> 04:31.662
♪ Give in to the boom

04:31.706 --> 04:34.448
♪ Don't lose your cool,
fighter jets ain't coming ♪

04:34.491 --> 04:37.320
♪ Oh, but if they do,
there's no use in running ♪

04:37.364 --> 04:40.454
♪ So get in the mood,
live until we're done in ♪

04:40.497 --> 04:43.108
♪ Give in to the boom

04:43.152 --> 04:45.937
♪ You can't duck and cover

04:45.981 --> 04:48.679
♪ When the world's
going under ♪

04:48.723 --> 04:51.726
♪ If the bomb chooses you

04:51.769 --> 04:54.685
♪ Give in to the boom

04:54.729 --> 04:57.034
♪ You can't duck and cover

04:57.079 --> 04:59.864
♪ When the world's
going under ♪

04:59.908 --> 05:02.824
♪ If the bomb chooses you

05:02.867 --> 05:05.653
♪ Give in to the boom

05:05.696 --> 05:07.872
[film clicking]

05:07.916 --> 05:10.745
[school bell rings]

05:10.788 --> 05:13.661
[indistinct chatter]

05:17.839 --> 05:19.449
- Pick me up at 7:00 tonight?

05:19.493 --> 05:21.016
- Yeah.

05:21.059 --> 05:24.149
Tonight, we need to talk.

05:31.679 --> 05:32.854
- [sighs]

05:32.897 --> 05:35.813
[upbeat music]

05:35.857 --> 05:42.994
♪

05:48.086 --> 05:53.178
- Have not saints lips
and holy palmers too?

05:53.222 --> 05:56.051
- Aye, pilgrim,
lips that--

05:56.094 --> 05:57.966
they must use in prayer.

05:58.009 --> 06:02.362
- O, then, dear saint,
let lips do what hands do.

06:02.405 --> 06:03.841
They pray.

06:03.885 --> 06:07.671
- This is painful to watch,
and I want them to fail.

06:07.715 --> 06:10.282
- Will they just get
to the part where they die?

06:10.326 --> 06:12.110
- Oh, so you're
talking to me now?

06:12.154 --> 06:13.982
- I think
you're being punished enough.

06:14.025 --> 06:16.854
- Cut! Stop! Stop!

06:16.898 --> 06:18.378
- I'm sorry.
Did I mess up a line?

06:18.421 --> 06:21.163
- No, you're fantastic.

06:21.206 --> 06:24.471
You're going to make grown
women reevaluate their lives!

06:24.514 --> 06:27.822
You make me feel like
I've made a mistake.

06:27.865 --> 06:30.520
- If you want
to cast someone else...

06:30.564 --> 06:34.916
- No,
because I do not make mistakes.

06:34.959 --> 06:37.875
The muse is only
challenging me,

06:37.919 --> 06:39.529
that trickster hag.

06:39.573 --> 06:41.052
Oh, God.

06:42.445 --> 06:44.534
Mm.

06:44.578 --> 06:47.319
You'll work with Lydia.

06:51.802 --> 06:53.282
- No.

06:53.325 --> 06:54.283
- Yes.

06:54.326 --> 06:55.502
- No.

06:55.545 --> 06:56.894
- Yes!

06:56.938 --> 06:59.941
Do not bring her back
until you have broken her.

06:59.984 --> 07:02.509
[school bell rings]

07:05.033 --> 07:07.296
- You're on your own.

07:07.339 --> 07:08.428
Dig?

07:08.471 --> 07:11.039
- Fine by me.
I don't need your help.

07:11.082 --> 07:13.302
Dig?
- I do.

07:13.345 --> 07:15.478
And frankly,
I cannot wait

07:15.522 --> 07:21.005
to see you do that
in front of all of them.

07:33.714 --> 07:35.019
[typewriter clattering]

07:35.063 --> 07:38.196
- Thanks, Mr. Daniels.

07:38.240 --> 07:39.894
- Ooh.

07:39.937 --> 07:41.199
Toodle-loo, Leonard.

07:41.243 --> 07:43.158
I'm off to canasta
with the girls.

07:43.201 --> 07:45.508
- Take them
for all they've got, Hilda.

07:45.552 --> 07:48.337
- Oh, an anonymous
little birdie told me

07:48.380 --> 07:50.600
that you bought one
of the first Lakeridge houses.

07:50.644 --> 07:53.429
The one with the rose bushes
on Sparrow Lane.

07:53.473 --> 07:55.039
- Guilty.

07:55.082 --> 07:56.998
I'm lucky Dick Aldridge cuts
deals for his son's teachers.

07:57.041 --> 07:59.087
- Barb will love it.

08:00.871 --> 08:02.482
And it was Eileen who told me.

08:02.525 --> 08:05.615
She's a terrible gossip.
Never trust her.

08:05.659 --> 08:07.269
- Nope.

08:12.361 --> 08:14.624
- My opinion piece
on the lack of women authors

08:14.668 --> 08:16.234
in Rydell's English curriculum.

08:16.278 --> 08:19.324
- [sighs]
You love to get me in trouble.

08:19.368 --> 08:21.326
- It has nothing
to do with you.

08:21.370 --> 08:23.241
I like writing for the paper.

08:23.285 --> 08:24.286
- Hmm.

08:26.375 --> 08:28.029
- Hey, beautiful.

08:28.072 --> 08:29.291
Why are you carrying
those heavy books

08:29.334 --> 08:30.945
when I got two hands
hanging useless

08:30.988 --> 08:32.294
off the end of my arms?

08:32.337 --> 08:33.861
- [chuckles]

08:33.904 --> 08:36.820
[upbeat music]

08:36.864 --> 08:38.256
♪

08:38.299 --> 08:40.215
- Say, Daddy,
what are you doing there?

08:40.258 --> 08:42.260
- "We need to talk."

08:42.304 --> 08:44.001
That can only mean one thing.

08:44.044 --> 08:45.437
- He's PG.

08:45.481 --> 08:47.135
Jane, you dog!

08:47.178 --> 08:48.484
- He's breaking things off!

08:48.528 --> 08:50.007
We aren't even
officially dating!

08:50.051 --> 08:51.531
- [groans]
- [yelps]

08:51.574 --> 08:54.185
- You have
what we in the medical field

08:54.229 --> 08:57.014
call being totally flipped.

08:57.058 --> 09:00.670
Tell us,
where did it begin?

09:00.714 --> 09:02.411
- I don't know.

09:02.454 --> 09:04.674
Catholicism?
- Catholicism...

09:04.718 --> 09:06.502
- Being uprooted
from New York.

09:06.546 --> 09:08.199
I always feel like
the rug is going

09:08.243 --> 09:10.071
to be pulled out
from underneath me.

09:10.114 --> 09:12.377
- Ah,
I can't take this anymore!

09:12.421 --> 09:15.337
He wants to ask you
to be his girl.

09:15.380 --> 09:16.904
- What?

09:16.947 --> 09:19.602
- My brother wants
to be your boyfriend.

09:19.646 --> 09:21.648
That's the bomb, OK?

09:21.691 --> 09:23.693
- Oh, that's a relief.

09:23.737 --> 09:26.000
- Hey.

09:26.043 --> 09:27.610
- Now, can we talk
about a real problem?

09:27.654 --> 09:29.656
I need help with my lines
with this stupid play!

09:29.699 --> 09:31.222
They've already
got me wearing a dress.

09:31.266 --> 09:32.876
I don't want to give them
another reason to laugh at me.

09:32.920 --> 09:34.399
- I can help.

09:34.443 --> 09:37.315
I am not an actor, nor do I
respect the profession,

09:37.359 --> 09:38.969
but I also feel like
I'd be great at it.

09:39.013 --> 09:40.449
- OK, you read Romeo's lines.

09:40.492 --> 09:43.104
- OK.
[clears throat]

09:43.147 --> 09:45.280
Have not saints lips
and holy...

09:45.323 --> 09:48.022
Ooh, this is boring.
I'm sorry.

09:48.065 --> 09:50.938
I have to return
to my first love: fashion.

09:50.981 --> 09:52.287
Mom!
- [gasps]

09:52.330 --> 09:54.506
Goodness, Nancy.
You don't have to yell.

09:54.550 --> 09:55.943
Got it right here.

09:55.986 --> 09:57.814
- Nancy worked all night
on these.

09:57.858 --> 09:59.947
- Hear that, girls?
All night.

09:59.990 --> 10:02.123
- Ah! What is it?

10:02.166 --> 10:04.865
- Your costumes!
[giggles]

10:04.908 --> 10:07.998
Olivia, you're a martian

10:08.042 --> 10:12.089
because
you're exploring new worlds.

10:12.133 --> 10:15.005
Jane, you're a werewolf

10:15.049 --> 10:18.313
because you are transforming
into something more interesting

10:18.356 --> 10:19.923
than you used to be.

10:19.967 --> 10:22.665
And, Cynthia,
you're an ant

10:22.709 --> 10:27.017
who got trapped in
an atomic experiment because...

10:27.061 --> 10:28.715
it's a cool costume
I wanted to make.

10:28.758 --> 10:30.847
- Thanks, but it's
two-for-one hot dog night

10:30.891 --> 10:32.283
at the drive-in.

10:32.327 --> 10:34.415
I can't eat six to eight
hot dogs with this thing on.

10:34.459 --> 10:37.637
- Thanks, Nancy, but I don't
want to look scary tonight.

10:37.680 --> 10:39.856
I've got a date!

10:39.900 --> 10:41.641
So does Olivia.

10:41.684 --> 10:44.469
- No, I don't!

10:44.513 --> 10:47.690
But I should look good
if it turns into one.

10:47.734 --> 10:50.345
I'm just gonna throw on some
cat ears and call it a night.

10:50.388 --> 10:52.521
- Are you serious?

10:52.564 --> 10:57.221
Halloween is about dressing up
and having fun, not boys.

10:57.265 --> 11:00.268
- Why not all the above?
What's your costume?

11:00.311 --> 11:01.748
- Swamp monster.

11:01.791 --> 11:05.447
You know what they say.
Dress for the job you want.

11:05.490 --> 11:07.623
- Or do the job you have.

11:11.061 --> 11:12.323
- [groans]

11:13.803 --> 11:15.109
All finished here?

11:15.152 --> 11:16.501
Thank you.

11:19.330 --> 11:22.116
- When you wave the white
flag, you want to be friends.

11:22.159 --> 11:24.466
- Hey there!
Open up!

11:24.509 --> 11:26.207
Come on out!
We're friends!

11:26.250 --> 11:29.384
[crowd yelling]

11:31.691 --> 11:33.954
- I'm scared!
- Don't worry. Don't worry.

11:33.997 --> 11:37.261
Anything that tries to kill you
has to kill me first.

11:37.305 --> 11:39.176
- What? What is this?

11:39.220 --> 11:40.395
Ugh!
- I'm a superhero.

11:40.438 --> 11:42.832
- What superhero?
- Please stop, Rosemary.

11:42.876 --> 11:44.529
- But you're wearing
a weird outfit.

11:44.573 --> 11:45.966
That's not the costume
we talked about.

11:46.009 --> 11:47.663
Now, we don't match!
- I don't want to walk around

11:47.707 --> 11:50.187
all night in a hospital gown!
It's embarrassing!

11:50.231 --> 11:51.667
I don't know why
I couldn't be a doctor.

11:51.711 --> 11:54.757
My dad's a doctor.
- He is?

11:54.801 --> 11:56.716
- How much
did this bike set you back?

11:56.759 --> 11:59.022
- A penny or two,
but it's worth it.

11:59.066 --> 12:00.632
- Run, lady!

12:00.676 --> 12:04.462
And take off your heels!
They're slowing you down!

12:04.506 --> 12:06.987
- You think
extraterrestrials are real?

12:07.030 --> 12:08.858
- Maybe,
but if they come down here

12:08.902 --> 12:10.033
looking for intelligent life,

12:10.077 --> 12:11.774
they're gonna be
very disappointed.

12:11.818 --> 12:13.384
- [chuckles]

12:16.170 --> 12:18.738
- Move!
You're blocking the screen.

12:18.781 --> 12:20.304
- Yeah, I don't want
to miss the part

12:20.348 --> 12:22.611
where they disintegrate the
guys with their laser beams.

12:22.654 --> 12:23.699
- How do you know
that's going to happen?

12:23.743 --> 12:25.701
Have you seen
this movie before?

12:25.745 --> 12:26.833
- I don't have to.

12:26.876 --> 12:29.139
I'm great
at predicting plot twists.

12:29.183 --> 12:31.315
[laser beam zapping]

12:33.665 --> 12:35.319
- Turn up the radio, everyone!

12:35.363 --> 12:37.495
Johnny Vavoom
is doing dedications!

12:38.192 --> 12:40.281
[radio static]

12:40.324 --> 12:41.935
- Hey there,
ghosts and goblins!

12:41.978 --> 12:43.937
Just 'cause the grim reaper
is on the prowl

12:43.980 --> 12:46.069
doesn't mean
romance has to be dead too.

12:46.113 --> 12:49.420
So to Polly from Orson:
"Won't you be my ghoul?"

12:49.464 --> 12:50.639
- [mockingly]
Won't you be my ghoul?

12:50.682 --> 12:52.162
- And from Bill to Edith:

12:52.206 --> 12:53.773
"No tricks.
You're a treat."

12:53.816 --> 12:56.950
And finally, to Nancy Nakagawa
from a secret admirer:

12:56.993 --> 12:59.300
"You are more special
than you know.

12:59.343 --> 13:01.824
This one's for you."

13:01.868 --> 13:03.434
- Nancy, that's you!

13:03.478 --> 13:05.785
- Congratulations!

13:05.828 --> 13:07.351
- That's stupid.

13:07.395 --> 13:09.832
I mean, who would
dedicate a song to me?

13:09.876 --> 13:11.529
- A real-life plot twist!

13:11.573 --> 13:13.444
Let me help you
figure it out, please?

13:13.488 --> 13:15.925
I got the goods...

13:15.969 --> 13:18.449
and the suspects to start.

13:18.493 --> 13:20.930
- ♪ Believe me,
I've got a case... ♪

13:20.974 --> 13:22.976
- It could be anyone.

13:23.019 --> 13:25.543
- ♪ Oh, Nancy

13:25.587 --> 13:27.850
♪ With a laughing face

13:27.894 --> 13:30.810
[laser beams zapping]

13:35.815 --> 13:37.251
- Jane.

13:37.294 --> 13:39.209
- Yes?

13:39.253 --> 13:41.037
Oh.

13:41.081 --> 13:42.647
- [chuckles] Hey!

13:42.691 --> 13:45.172
Eyes on the alien invasion.

13:45.215 --> 13:46.390
- As long
as they don't beam down

13:46.434 --> 13:47.914
and ruin the election tomorrow.

13:47.957 --> 13:49.219
- Relax.

13:49.263 --> 13:50.786
You're gonna win.

13:50.830 --> 13:53.615
And hey, maybe you can
make a few corrections

13:53.658 --> 13:56.270
to my attendance record
when you're in office.

13:56.313 --> 13:57.619
- [chuckles]

13:57.662 --> 13:59.316
I should probably focus
on trying

13:59.360 --> 14:01.449
to change the things
I promised to first.

14:01.492 --> 14:03.799
- Yeah, and I'm gonna help.

14:03.843 --> 14:06.628
We are gonna rule the school
this year.

14:06.671 --> 14:09.805
- Um, we?

14:09.849 --> 14:14.201
- Yeah, that's what I wanted
to talk to you about.

14:14.244 --> 14:16.116
We're good together.

14:16.159 --> 14:18.335
I like you more than
any other girl I've ever met,

14:18.379 --> 14:21.121
besides my mom and my sisters.

14:21.164 --> 14:24.298
I mean, differently
than my mom and my sisters.

14:24.341 --> 14:25.995
Obviously.
I'm sorry.

14:26.039 --> 14:28.432
I don't know why I'm talking
about my mom and my sisters.

14:28.476 --> 14:29.956
What I'm trying to say is...

14:33.089 --> 14:34.221
- Richie, I--

14:34.264 --> 14:37.398
[evil laughter]

14:38.616 --> 14:41.010
- It's insane
to vote for Jane!

14:41.054 --> 14:43.273
Vote for Buddy!

14:45.580 --> 14:47.538
[car horns honking]

14:47.582 --> 14:48.539
- Who's doing that?
Turn it off!

14:48.583 --> 14:51.281
- Tonight, party at Lakeridge.

14:51.325 --> 14:54.981
[evil laughter]

14:55.024 --> 14:56.852
- What the hell was that?

14:56.896 --> 14:58.332
- A bomb.

14:58.375 --> 14:59.986
- [cackling]

15:02.510 --> 15:04.425
- The Socs think
they can just throw a bash

15:04.468 --> 15:06.993
before the election
to get everyone on their side?

15:07.036 --> 15:08.559
- Looks like it's working.

15:08.603 --> 15:10.474
What are we gonna do?

15:10.518 --> 15:13.260
- Can you take me
to that address?

15:13.303 --> 15:14.696
- I'm here to serve.

15:14.739 --> 15:17.873
[classic rock music]

15:17.917 --> 15:19.962
♪

15:20.006 --> 15:21.311
- I'll catch up!

15:24.967 --> 15:27.187
I'll be right there!

15:27.230 --> 15:28.362
Come on!

15:34.411 --> 15:36.674
- So Buddy's dad
built all this, huh?

15:36.718 --> 15:39.939
- I think Buddy's dad
hired people to build all this.

15:39.982 --> 15:43.072
- Gotta admit, though,
these are some nice shacks.

15:50.079 --> 15:51.385
- Yeah.

15:53.430 --> 15:56.564
[indistinct chatter]

16:12.319 --> 16:13.842
- Whoop!

16:13.885 --> 16:17.106
Lucky for you girls, we're
all stocked up for tonight.

16:17.150 --> 16:19.152
Pick your poison.

16:19.195 --> 16:20.892
Eggs?

16:20.936 --> 16:21.937
- TP?

16:21.981 --> 16:23.330
- Water hose
through the window?

16:23.373 --> 16:25.201
- With enough time, we can
disassemble Buddy's car

16:25.245 --> 16:27.899
and reassemble it
on the roof.

16:27.943 --> 16:30.554
- Oh, um, well,

16:30.598 --> 16:32.774
I was thinking
something more like

16:32.817 --> 16:35.429
we get into the party and then
figure it out from there.

16:35.472 --> 16:36.734
- How are we gonna get in?

16:36.778 --> 16:39.607
They'll kick us all out
on sight.

16:39.650 --> 16:41.000
- [clears throat]

16:43.654 --> 16:45.265
♪ Fa-la-la-la-la

16:45.308 --> 16:47.441
♪ I love Halloween

16:50.096 --> 16:53.012
- OK, everyone,
follow my lead.

16:54.970 --> 16:57.059
- Me and the guys are
gonna sneak in the back.

16:57.103 --> 16:59.322
- You know what?
Why don't you stay out here?

16:59.366 --> 17:02.456
You're driving the getaway car.
You need to be ready.

17:02.499 --> 17:05.111
- Yeah, it's cool.
I'll just wait then.

17:05.154 --> 17:06.808
- OK.

17:18.037 --> 17:19.951
- Ugh, what are you
supposed to be?

17:19.994 --> 17:21.344
- I don't know.

17:21.387 --> 17:24.478
I just cut up my undershirt
with my pocketknife.

17:26.001 --> 17:28.569
- Go ahead.
I'll meet you inside.

17:40.102 --> 17:43.453
- Welcome to Ry-hell,

17:43.497 --> 17:47.066
the land of no liberty.

17:47.109 --> 17:49.503
Tonight, we take you
on a journey

17:49.546 --> 17:54.856
where you will see the dark,
dreary future that awaits you

17:54.899 --> 17:56.945
if you vote for Jane Facciano.

17:58.860 --> 18:01.776
Once the Pink Ladies
are your leaders,

18:01.819 --> 18:04.431
this will be your lunch.

18:04.474 --> 18:07.086
Did anyone order brain?

18:07.129 --> 18:10.350
- [cackles]

18:10.393 --> 18:12.308
[coughs]

18:12.352 --> 18:14.745
Do you mind bringing me a soda?
It's really hot in here.

18:14.789 --> 18:16.834
- You can drink on your break.
- I know.

18:16.878 --> 18:20.621
But it's hard to breathe--
- Moving along!

18:20.664 --> 18:25.191
Under the reign of Jane,
this will be your uniform.

18:25.234 --> 18:28.629
Both: She said it'd be fun
for everyone.

18:28.672 --> 18:32.720
- And this will be
the Rydell flag.

18:34.461 --> 18:36.680
- Communism? How original.
- Hmm.

18:36.724 --> 18:39.118
- What was that, werewolf?

18:39.161 --> 18:42.512
- [growls]

18:42.556 --> 18:44.253
Where's the punch?

18:44.297 --> 18:45.820
- Oh, through the streamers.

18:45.863 --> 18:47.082
Straight back.
Can't miss it.

18:47.126 --> 18:48.692
If you hit the bathroom,
you've gone too far.

18:48.736 --> 18:52.348
Welcome to Ry-hell!

18:52.392 --> 18:53.523
♪

18:53.567 --> 18:56.352
- ♪ Crazy, man, crazy

18:56.396 --> 18:58.963
♪ Crazy, man, crazy

18:59.007 --> 19:01.227
♪ Crazy, man, crazy

19:01.270 --> 19:04.447
♪ Oh,
when the music's gone, gone ♪

19:04.491 --> 19:05.492
♪ Crazy, man, crazy

19:05.535 --> 19:07.450
- Wow.
Look at that costume.

19:07.494 --> 19:10.279
[chuckles]
You're?

19:10.323 --> 19:12.063
- The solar system.

19:12.107 --> 19:14.196
- Hey, our costumes
kind of go together!

19:14.240 --> 19:15.719
- Yeah.
- Hey!

19:15.763 --> 19:17.112
We're bobbing for apples.

19:17.156 --> 19:19.027
Loser has to drink
the spit water.

19:19.070 --> 19:21.421
- But we're cheating, so
the nerds are having to chug.

19:21.464 --> 19:22.770
Come see!
- Guys!

19:22.813 --> 19:24.902
Guys, don't do that!
Don't--

19:24.946 --> 19:26.513
Hey, I'm sorry.
I got to go deal with that.

19:26.556 --> 19:27.731
But find me later

19:27.775 --> 19:29.037
so I can give you
a ride home tonight, OK?

19:29.080 --> 19:30.517
It can get pretty crazy
out there.

19:30.560 --> 19:32.562
- OK, sure.

19:32.606 --> 19:33.781
- Neil!

19:36.523 --> 19:38.655
- Wait.
You're breaking up with me?

19:38.699 --> 19:40.179
- Rosemary, it's over!

19:40.222 --> 19:43.312
You're bossy, you're mean,
and you never listen to me!

19:43.356 --> 19:46.054
- What?

19:46.097 --> 19:47.186
Ugh!

19:49.579 --> 19:52.278
Hi. How are you?

19:52.321 --> 19:55.194
[laughs]
You're so funny.

19:57.196 --> 19:59.459
- [gasps]

19:59.502 --> 20:01.504
That's our ticket.

20:01.548 --> 20:03.158
Mm-hmm.

20:03.202 --> 20:05.334
I have a plan.

20:05.378 --> 20:06.857
Where's Olivia?

20:06.901 --> 20:08.772
- Probably in the can.

20:08.816 --> 20:10.339
- Cynthia, you're with me.

20:10.383 --> 20:12.167
Nancy, you'll be the lookout.

20:12.211 --> 20:13.516
Potato...

20:13.560 --> 20:15.779
I'm still not sure
why you're here.

20:15.823 --> 20:22.960
♪

20:33.275 --> 20:34.276
- [grunts]
- Sorry!

20:34.320 --> 20:35.495
Good golly, I'm so sorry.

20:35.538 --> 20:37.584
- All right,
back to the secret admirer.

20:37.627 --> 20:39.368
First rule of plot twists:

20:39.412 --> 20:41.892
the murderer is always
someone you know.

20:41.936 --> 20:45.418
- My secret admirer
is not a murderer.

20:45.461 --> 20:47.463
I don't think.

20:47.507 --> 20:50.727
- Is there anyone you've had
a connection with lately?

20:52.729 --> 20:54.601
- Wally and Rosemary
just broke up?

20:54.644 --> 20:55.993
Ooh!

20:59.170 --> 21:00.128
- Oh.

21:00.171 --> 21:02.652
- Hey.
How are you doing?

21:02.696 --> 21:04.524
- Nancy?
- No names!

21:04.567 --> 21:05.960
Listen, kid,

21:06.003 --> 21:08.005
I felt a connection out there
in the field too,

21:08.049 --> 21:11.139
but it was strictly horse
to athlete.

21:11.182 --> 21:13.402
You didn't have to break up
with your girlfriend for me.

21:13.446 --> 21:15.099
- I didn't.

21:15.143 --> 21:16.971
Look, I haven't
told anyone this yet,

21:17.014 --> 21:20.670
but I'm actually
kind of sweet on...

21:23.673 --> 21:26.067
- OK, egg the school,

21:26.110 --> 21:28.635
TP McGee's,
and fireworks at Nicholson's?

21:28.678 --> 21:29.984
- Let's do McGee's last.

21:30.027 --> 21:31.333
Let the traffic clear up.

21:31.377 --> 21:33.640
- Uh, fellas?

21:33.683 --> 21:36.338
At least
we still got the fireworks.

21:36.382 --> 21:38.732
- What's wrong with us?
It's Halloween!

21:38.775 --> 21:40.037
T-Birds are supposed
to be kings!

21:40.081 --> 21:40.951
- I've been thinking
the same thing.

21:40.995 --> 21:42.126
What are we missing?

21:42.170 --> 21:45.042
- The girls.
- [scoffs] That is it.

21:48.394 --> 21:49.395
I'm going in.

21:50.918 --> 21:53.224
Hey!
- Oh!

21:53.268 --> 21:56.097
- Can I borrow that?
- Sure.

21:56.140 --> 21:57.881
- Keep an eye on the cars.

21:57.925 --> 21:59.927
- Didn't Jane say
to wait out here?

21:59.970 --> 22:02.756
- Jane's my girl,
not my boss.

22:15.116 --> 22:16.813
- Are we almost done?

22:16.857 --> 22:19.947
These arms keep
making passes at people.

22:19.990 --> 22:21.905
- I just have to get down
to the basement.

22:21.949 --> 22:24.865
The problem is, you can't
hear anything down there.

22:27.650 --> 22:30.261
That's it! OK,
when the band is between songs,

22:30.305 --> 22:34.178
you call down to me through the
laundry chute, and I'll start.

22:49.890 --> 22:51.935
- Hi, Cynthia.

22:51.979 --> 22:54.416
- What?
How'd you know it was me?

22:54.460 --> 22:55.983
- I've studied your gait.

22:56.026 --> 22:57.854
You walk like
a neurotic pigeon.

22:57.898 --> 22:59.465
- What's your costume?

22:59.508 --> 23:02.555
- The American dream.

23:02.598 --> 23:03.512
- Funny.

23:03.556 --> 23:06.167
[finger snap]

23:06.210 --> 23:07.995
Wait!

23:08.038 --> 23:10.301
I really need your help
with the play.

23:10.345 --> 23:11.825
- Hmm.

23:11.868 --> 23:13.957
The rube has returned
to her liege.

23:14.001 --> 23:15.742
- Come on.
I'm begging.

23:15.785 --> 23:17.221
Besides, Mr. Vaughan says

23:17.265 --> 23:19.354
we are only as strong
as our weakest link,

23:19.398 --> 23:23.489
so if I blow it,
you look bad too.

23:27.884 --> 23:30.452
- Fine. Go.

23:30.496 --> 23:34.674
- Aye, pilgrim, lips
that they must use in prayer.

23:34.717 --> 23:38.112
- O, then, dear saint,
let lips do what hands do.

23:38.155 --> 23:42.595
They pray, grant thou,
lest faith turn to despair.

23:42.638 --> 23:45.641
- Saints do not move.

23:45.685 --> 23:46.903
- It's that line.

23:46.947 --> 23:48.775
Yeah, you get all strange
when you say it.

23:48.818 --> 23:49.993
- No, I don't.

23:51.386 --> 23:54.302
- The kiss.

23:54.345 --> 23:56.304
Are you nervous about the kiss?

23:56.347 --> 23:57.827
- Pfft!

23:59.568 --> 24:00.700
Yes.

24:00.743 --> 24:01.788
- [scoffs]

24:01.831 --> 24:03.093
- I've never done that before.

24:03.137 --> 24:04.660
- Stage kisses are meaningless.

24:04.704 --> 24:07.358
It's like kissing the wall.

24:07.402 --> 24:08.751
I can show you.

24:08.795 --> 24:11.667
- You mean, here?

24:11.711 --> 24:13.016
[whispers] Now?

24:13.060 --> 24:14.322
- The quicker
you get something over with,

24:14.365 --> 24:17.499
the less of a deal it becomes
in your mind.

24:17.543 --> 24:19.196
- OK.

24:22.635 --> 24:27.466
Saints do not move, though
grant, for prayers' sake.

24:27.509 --> 24:31.861
- Then move not while
my prayer's effect I take.

24:31.905 --> 24:34.821
[tender music]

24:34.864 --> 24:41.523
♪

24:41.567 --> 24:43.873
- ♪ I heard
about this feeling ♪

24:43.917 --> 24:46.093
♪ I've never felt before

24:46.136 --> 24:50.227
♪ Spotlights reflecting
on my eyes ♪

24:50.271 --> 24:52.273
♪ Something's overflowing

24:52.316 --> 24:54.493
♪ It shouldn't
feel this right ♪

24:54.536 --> 24:59.106
♪ Imagining's way better
than life ♪

24:59.149 --> 25:03.023
♪ All this time,
had no idea ♪

25:03.066 --> 25:05.112
♪ I'd lose myself
inside the words ♪

25:05.155 --> 25:07.375
♪ And find myself
in a new world ♪

25:07.418 --> 25:11.553
♪ There's nothing
that I can't feel ♪

25:11.597 --> 25:15.905
♪ How can these emotions be
way more real than anything? ♪

25:15.949 --> 25:20.562
♪ Up here,
we're merely players ♪

25:20.606 --> 25:24.218
♪ But playing's real
when you commit to danger ♪

25:24.261 --> 25:28.309
♪ The love,
the fear, the anger ♪

25:28.352 --> 25:30.572
♪ Feels somehow real

25:30.616 --> 25:33.488
♪ Though
we are merely players ♪

25:33.532 --> 25:36.230
♪

25:36.273 --> 25:38.362
- ♪ I know just
what you're feeling ♪

25:38.406 --> 25:40.321
♪ I've had that dream before

25:40.364 --> 25:44.717
♪ Had it every night
of my life ♪

25:44.760 --> 25:48.590
♪ Underneath the lights,
you can find your truest form ♪

25:48.634 --> 25:53.203
There's so much honesty
in the lie ♪

25:53.247 --> 25:57.251
both: ♪ Hollywood has no idea

25:57.294 --> 26:00.254
♪ That everything they're
looking for is right here ♪

26:00.297 --> 26:01.603
♪ We'll make it real

26:01.647 --> 26:05.868
♪ There's nothing
that we can't feel ♪

26:05.912 --> 26:10.003
♪ We've just got to move on in,
give everything without fear ♪

26:10.046 --> 26:14.398
♪ Up here,
we're merely players ♪

26:14.442 --> 26:18.577
♪ But playing's real
when you commit to danger ♪

26:18.620 --> 26:22.798
♪ The love,
the fear, the anger ♪

26:22.842 --> 26:25.018
♪ Feels somehow real

26:25.061 --> 26:27.498
♪ Though
we are merely players ♪

26:27.542 --> 26:30.066
♪

26:30.110 --> 26:34.462
- ♪ You're
the new Greta Garbo ♪

26:34.505 --> 26:39.293
- ♪ And you're Marlon Brando

26:39.336 --> 26:43.427
- ♪ Hollywood has no idea

26:43.471 --> 26:47.649
both: ♪ Up here,
we're merely players ♪

26:47.693 --> 26:51.653
♪ But playing's real
when you commit to danger ♪

26:51.697 --> 26:55.875
♪ The love,
the fear, the anger ♪

26:55.918 --> 26:58.138
♪ Feels somehow real

26:58.181 --> 27:00.096
♪ Though
we are merely players ♪

27:00.140 --> 27:03.970
- ♪ Up here,
we're merely players ♪

27:04.013 --> 27:08.365
♪ But a play is real
when you commit to danger ♪

27:08.409 --> 27:12.282
♪ The love,
the fear, the anger ♪

27:12.326 --> 27:14.545
♪ Feels somehow real

27:14.589 --> 27:16.373
♪ Though
we are merely players ♪

27:16.417 --> 27:19.420
both: ♪ Hollywood has no idea

27:24.599 --> 27:26.862
- Wow.

27:26.906 --> 27:28.951
So that's acting.

27:28.995 --> 27:31.693
- Yeah.
[clears throat]

27:31.737 --> 27:33.608
- It felt so real.

27:33.652 --> 27:36.089
- That's--
that is why people love it.

27:37.307 --> 27:39.527
- I get it now.

27:39.570 --> 27:42.661
Wait.
Does this mean I'm a thespian?

27:44.140 --> 27:45.664
- [sighs]

27:49.885 --> 27:52.801
[door creaks]

27:56.370 --> 27:59.547
[eerie music]

27:59.590 --> 28:06.467
♪

28:12.168 --> 28:13.343
- Whoa!
- Aah!

28:15.258 --> 28:18.000
What are you doing here?

28:18.044 --> 28:20.742
- This is my house.

28:20.786 --> 28:22.004
What are you doing here?

28:22.048 --> 28:24.441
- I'm sorry.
Didn't even know it was yours.

28:26.748 --> 28:28.358
Painting?

28:28.402 --> 28:29.751
- How did you guess?

28:29.795 --> 28:31.797
[laughter]

28:35.235 --> 28:37.759
Barb didn't care
for the turquoise.

28:37.803 --> 28:40.588
She said it's loud.

28:43.286 --> 28:45.767
- I like it.

28:45.811 --> 28:48.422
- Yeah, me too.

28:48.465 --> 28:51.512
But now we're doing beige.
- Mm.

28:54.907 --> 28:57.692
- Want a tour?

28:57.736 --> 28:59.259
- Sure.

29:10.139 --> 29:11.097
- Sorry, Nancy.
- It's OK.

29:11.140 --> 29:12.141
I was hoping it wasn't you too.

29:12.185 --> 29:14.578
Nothing personal.

29:14.622 --> 29:17.407
We're never going
to find this guy.

29:17.451 --> 29:19.758
- Maybe there's a clue hidden
in the lyric of the song.

29:19.801 --> 29:21.020
- OK.
- Yeah.

29:21.063 --> 29:22.673
- "Summer could
take some lessons from her."

29:22.717 --> 29:24.458
- Bingo.
Who'd you meet this summer?

29:24.501 --> 29:27.113
- Nobody.
I loathe picnics and beaches.

29:27.156 --> 29:28.810
- What about the title?

29:28.854 --> 29:31.421
"Nancy with the Laughing Face"?
What makes you laugh?

29:31.465 --> 29:33.336
- Bugs Bunny,
and only Bugs Bunny.

29:33.380 --> 29:34.947
- [chuckles]
Yeah, that guy's hilarious.

29:34.990 --> 29:36.383
But come on.

29:36.426 --> 29:37.950
Can you think of anyone?
- No.

29:37.993 --> 29:40.474
This is probably just
someone pulling a prank on me.

29:40.517 --> 29:42.345
All the boys at the school
think I'm weird.

29:42.389 --> 29:44.217
- Come on.
You're not weird.

29:44.260 --> 29:46.001
You're...

29:46.045 --> 29:50.179
OK, you're a little weird, but
that just means you're unique.

29:50.223 --> 29:52.312
All the guys want
a unique girl.

29:54.575 --> 29:56.229
Ooh, let's look in there!

29:59.928 --> 30:02.844
- Come on, Cynthia.

30:02.888 --> 30:06.239
What is the holdup?

30:06.282 --> 30:07.631
You know what?

30:10.460 --> 30:13.028
Ladies and gentlemen.

30:13.072 --> 30:16.031
[soft rock music]

30:16.075 --> 30:19.556
♪

30:19.600 --> 30:23.386
- ♪ Leave my baby alone

30:23.430 --> 30:25.562
♪ Please tend
to your own business ♪

30:25.606 --> 30:29.044
♪ And leave my baby alone

30:29.088 --> 30:30.567
- Ooh!

30:32.439 --> 30:34.833
[mic feedback]

30:37.139 --> 30:38.532
[groaning]

30:38.575 --> 30:41.361
- Ladies and gentlemen,

30:41.404 --> 30:43.580
I have an announcement

30:43.624 --> 30:46.540
about the real Ry-hell.

30:46.583 --> 30:48.194
The one you're living in now.

30:48.237 --> 30:51.458
The one ruled by the Socs.

30:51.501 --> 30:53.808
- [whispers] What is going on?
- I don't know.

30:53.852 --> 30:57.464
- These evildoers may
invite you to swell parties

30:57.507 --> 31:00.641
once a year,
right before the election,

31:00.684 --> 31:03.339
only so that you'll forget
about all the times

31:03.383 --> 31:05.994
they've ignored
and tormented you!

31:06.038 --> 31:09.041
- That's not true.
We consider all of you friends.

31:09.084 --> 31:10.216
Right, Louise?

31:10.259 --> 31:11.870
- It's Lucille!

31:11.913 --> 31:14.350
[crowd murmuring]

31:14.394 --> 31:16.439
- The voice is right
about being tormented!

31:16.483 --> 31:18.964
I just drank a gallon
of spit water.

31:19.007 --> 31:20.748
[laughter]
Cheaters!

31:20.791 --> 31:21.880
- Don't worry!

31:21.923 --> 31:26.014
That voice is all
a part of the show

31:26.058 --> 31:28.625
because it would be scary

31:28.669 --> 31:32.020
if any of that was really true.

